items.title: Accenture beats third-quarter revenue estimates
items.description: Accenture beat Wall Street estimates for third-quarter revenue on Friday, driven by growing demand for the consulting giant's AI-driven services from enterprise customers.

items.title: Indian Banks' earnings growth forecast halved amid economic caution and high deposit costs
items.description: Indian banks are facing a significant slowdown in earnings growth, potentially halving to 6.5% in FY26 due to a cautious economy and reduced core profits. Muted credit demand, high deposit costs, and RBI's measures to control unsecured lending contribute to this deceleration. However, a rebound to 16.1% is expected in FY27 with anticipated rate cuts and improved demand.

items.title: SpiceJet Q4 Results: PAT jumps 173% YoY to highest-ever quarterly profit of Rs 325 crore
items.description: Spicejet announced a significant profit increase for the March quarter. The airline's standalone profit after tax rose 173% YoY. This marks their highest ever quarterly profit. Spicejet also reported a full-year net profit after seven years. Improved yields and cost optimization drove the growth. The company's Chairman, Ajay Singh, expressed confidence in Spicejet's sustainable growth.
